direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods return collections (Set for keys, Collection for values) that are backed by the map, reflecting changes in the map.
Both methods return sets (keySet returns a set of keys, entrySet returns a set of entries) that are composited from the underlying maps.
Both methods involve operations on the composite maps, with keySet accessing keys and removeComposited modifying the composite maps.

enhanced_by.reason: Adding a map to the composite affects the state of the CompositeMap, which is relevant for keySet as it depends on the composite maps.
Putting a key-value pair into the map affects the key set, making it necessary to call keySet after such operations.
Both methods (keySet and containsValue) handle the presence of elements in the map, making containsValue useful for asserting the state of the map after keySet operations.
